Analysis of mouse retinal epigenetic data (GLDS-203): Low dose irradiation and hindlimb unloading microgravity in mice¶

Overview¶

NASA GeneLab is a comprehensive database that provided access to space-related omics datasets. GeneLab dataset GLDS-203 is obtained from a ground-based experiment that uses rodent models to evaluate damage in eye induced by prolonged low-dose radiation and simulated microgravity. Here, we analyze methylation data from female mice subjected to irradiation and/or microgravity with tissues collected at 7 days, 1 or 4 month following exposure to radiation and/or microgravity.

Dataset¶

  • https://genelab-data.ndc.nasa.gov/genelab/accession/GLDS-203/: Low dose (0.04 Gy) irradiation (LDR) and hindlimb unloading (HLU) microgravity in mice: retina transcriptomic and epigenomic data

References¶

  • https://nbis-workshop-epigenomics.readthedocs.io/en/latest/content/tutorials/methylationSeq/Seq_Tutorial.html
  • https://bmcgenomics.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/s12864-019-5880-1

#Function to summarise % methylation over different region types
summariseRegion <- function (data, type)
{
    pm_means=as.data.frame(colMeans(as.data.frame(percMethylation(data)))) %>% 
            tibble::rownames_to_column('Sample') %>% 
            dplyr::mutate(Group=gsub("Mmu.*RTN_","",Sample)) %>% 
            dplyr::mutate(Group=gsub("_Rep.*","",Group)) %>% 
            dplyr::mutate(Group=ifelse(grepl("HLLC_IRC", Group),"Control",Group)) %>%
            `colnames<-`(c("Sample", "MeanMeth", "Group")) %>%
            dplyr::mutate(Type=type)
    return(pm_means)
    
}

In [ ]:
##Read in, process, filter and normalize individual Bismark coverage files for all samples in each timepoint/exposure.
##Creates individual methylKit objects for each group that are then used for diff methylation.
allSamples<-fread("/home/pkothiya/trrac/data/studies/GLDS-203/methylation/nf/run3/results/bismark_methylation_calls/methylation_coverage/samples_all.tsv",header=T,sep="\t")
for (i in 1:length(timepoints)){
    for (j in 1:length(cases)){
        #Rtmp space runs out if not emptied; need to find another solution
        print(unlink("/tmp/Rtmp*",recursive=TRUE))
        print(paste0("meth_",timepoints[i],"_",cases[j]))
        samples<- allSamples %>% dplyr::filter(TimePoint==timepoints[i] & (Group=="Control" | Group==cases[j]))
        samples$Type<-ifelse(grepl("Control",samples$Group),0,1)
        myobj=methRead(as.list(paste0("/home/pkothiya/trrac/data/studies/GLDS-203/methylation/nf/run3/results/bismark_methylation_calls/methylation_coverage/",samples$File)),
           sample.id=as.list(samples$SampleName),
           pipeline = "bismarkCoverage",
           assembly="mm10",
           treatment=as.vector(samples$Type),
           context="CpG",
           mincov=5
           )
        
        ##Uncomment for obtaining differentially methylated regions
        #tiles <- tileMethylCounts(myobj,win.size=100,step.size=100,cov.bases=1)
        #filtered.myobj=filterByCoverage(tiles,lo.count=5,lo.perc=NULL,
                                      #hi.count=NULL,hi.perc=99.9)
        
        filtered.myobj=filterByCoverage(myobj,lo.count=5,lo.perc=NULL,
                                      hi.count=NULL,hi.perc=99.9)
        norm.filtered.myobj <- normalizeCoverage(filtered.myobj, method = "median")
        meth<-unite(norm.filtered.myobj, destrand = FALSE)
        assign(paste0("meth_",timepoints[i],"_",cases[j]), meth)
        myobj<-myobj.filt.norm<-meth<-NULL
    }
}

        labels_colors(p) <- colors_to_use[order.dendrogram(p)]
        plot(p, main = paste0(timepoints[i],"_",cases[j]))
        }
    }

        myDiff<-meth<-NULL
        }
    }

#Generate chr-based diff methylation plots, and overall methylation in CpG sites for each region and repeat type
par(mfrow=c(3,3))
options(repr.plot.width=20, repr.plot.height=12)
options(warn=-1)
k=0
for (i in 1:length(timepoints)){
    for (j in 1:length(cases)){
        k=k+1
        print(paste0("diff_",timepoints[i],"_",cases[j]))
        myDiff<-get(paste0("myDiff_",timepoints[i],"_",cases[j]))
        myDiff5p.hyper=getMethylDiff(myDiff,difference=10,qvalue=0.05,type="hyper")
        print(dim(myDiff5p.hyper))
        myDiff5p.hypo=getMethylDiff(myDiff,difference=10,qvalue=0.05,type="hypo")
        print(dim(myDiff5p.hypo))
        #all differentially methylated bases
        myDiff5p=getMethylDiff(myDiff,difference=10,qvalue=0.05)
        diffMethPerChr(myDiff,qvalue.cutoff=0.05, meth.cutoff=10)
        
        #Overall methylation in sites associated with each region type
        meth<-get(paste0("meth_",timepoints[i],"_",cases[j]))
        cpgiAndPromoter<-GenomicRanges::intersect(gene.obj$promoters,cpg.obj$CpGi,ignore.strand = TRUE)
        promoters=summariseRegion(regionCounts(meth,gene.obj$promoters,cov.bases = 3),"Promoter")
        exons=summariseRegion(regionCounts(meth,gene.obj$exons,cov.bases = 3),"Exon")
        introns=summariseRegion(regionCounts(meth,gene.obj$introns,cov.bases = 3),"Intron")
        tss=summariseRegion(regionCounts(meth,gene.obj$TSSes),"TSS")
        cpgi=summariseRegion(regionCounts(meth,cpg.obj$CpGi,cov.bases = 3),"CpGI")
        cpgsh=summariseRegion(regionCounts(meth,cpg.obj$shores,cov.bases = 3),"CpGSh")
        promincpg=summariseRegion(regionCounts(meth,cpgiAndPromoter,cov.bases = 3),"Promoter\nCpGI")
        glocalcpg=summariseRegion(meth,"Global")

        data<-rbind(cpgi,cpgsh,promoters,promincpg,exons,introns,tss,glocalcpg)

        plot_tmp<-ggbarplot(data, x = "Type", y = "MeanMeth", add = "mean_sd",
          fill="Group",palette = c("#00AFBB", "#E7B800"), 
          position = position_dodge(0.75))+
          stat_compare_means(aes(group = Group, label=..p.format..), method = "t.test", tip.length = 0.01) + 
          font("xlab", size = 16, face="bold")+
          font("ylab", size = 16, face="bold")+
          font("xy.text", size = 14) +
          font("legend.title", size=16,face = "bold")+
          font("legend.text", size=12)
        assign(paste0("reg_",k), plot_tmp)
        }
    }

#Convert methylDiff object to GRanges and annotate differentially methylated regions; save file with DML or DMR
data<- data.frame(Type=character(),
                 V1=integer(), 
                 Group=character(), 
                 stringsAsFactors=FALSE) 

k=0
for (i in 1:length(timepoints)){
    for (j in 1:length(cases)){
        k=k+1
        print(paste0("diff_",timepoints[i],"_",cases[j]))
        myDiff<-get(paste0("myDiff_",timepoints[i],"_",cases[j]))
        
        #All sites with q-value<0.1
        myDiffFilt=getMethylDiff(myDiff,difference=0,qvalue=0.1)
        
        if(dim(myDiffFilt)[1]>0){
        myDiffFilt$Type<-paste0(timepoints[i],"_",cases[j])
        if(k==1){
            allDiffs<-myDiffFilt
        }
        else{
            allDiffs<-rbind(allDiffs, myDiffFilt)
        }
        print(dim(myDiffFilt))
        }
    }
}
allDiffs<-merge(allDiffs,annotLookup,by.x=c("feature.name"),by.y=c("ensembl_transcript_id"))
write.table(allDiffs, "GLDS-203_dml_orig.tsv", quote=FALSE, row.names=F, sep="\t")

# Create Manhattan plots
options(repr.plot.width=12, repr.plot.height=12)
par(mfrow=c(3,3))
k=0
for (i in 1:length(timepoints)){
    for (j in 1:length(cases)){
        k=k+1
        df<-allDiffs %>% dplyr::filter(Type==paste0(timepoints[i],"_",cases[j]) & qvalue<0.05 & abs(meth.diff)>5 & chr!="chrY")
        df$chr<-ifelse(df$chr=="chrX","chr21",df$chr)
        df$chr<-as.numeric(gsub("chr","",df$chr))
        df$CpG=paste(df$chr,df$start,df$external_gene_name,sep="_")
        print(manhattan(as.data.frame(df), bp="start", chr="chr", snp="CpG", p="qvalue", annotatePval = 0.05,
                        genomewideline = FALSE, suggestiveline = TRUE,main=paste0(timepoints[i],"_",cases[j])))
        }
    }
